{
  "texts": [
    "We briefly review it in this section, and we will relate it to another description used in [Moc25], namely in terms of 'deformation data', in the next section.",
    "We will present everything in our case of interest, where Σ = P 1 (C) is the Riemann sphere, and the only marked point is at ∞.",
    "However, the generalisation to an arbitrary Riemann surface with one or several marked points is not difficult.",
    "Let (E, ∇) be a connection on the affine line and V 0 → I the corresponding formal local system, with irregular class Θ.",
    "Let I ⊂ I be the finite subcover of ∂ consisting of the active circles of V 0."
  ]
}